{"label":"SVG - Intro","id":"svg","list":[{"label":"Multiple Choice Question","type":"mcq","id":"test","commonData":{"title":"Multiple Choice Question","allowFrac":false},"data":[{"questions":[{"qText":"What does SVG stand for?","options":"scalable vector graphics\nsimple vector graphics\nstandard visual graphics\nsmall variable graphics"},{"qText":"Which file format is SVG based on?","options":"xml\nhtml\njson\ncss"},{"qText":"Which SVG element is used to draw a rectangle?","options":"<rect> ,<square> ,<box>, <rectangle>"},{"qText":"Which SVG element is used to draw a circle?","options":"<circle>, <ellipse>, <round>, <dot>"},{"qText":"Which SVG element is used to draw an ellipse?","options":"<ellipse>, <circle>, <oval>, <round>"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Which SVG element is used to draw a straight line?","options":"<line>, <path>, <stroke>, <polyline>"},{"qText":"Which SVG element is used to draw connected straight lines?","options":"<polyline>, <polygon>, <path>, <line>"},{"qText":"Which SVG element is used to draw a closed shape with multiple sides?","options":"<polygon>, <polyline>, <path>, <rect>"},{"qText":"Which SVG element is used to define text?","options":"<text>, <label>, <string>, <words>"},{"qText":"Which attribute is used to define the fill color in SVG shapes?","options":"fill\nbackground\ncolor\nstyle"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Which attribute is used to define the line color of an SVG shape?","options":"stroke\nline\nborder\noutline"},{"qText":"Which attribute is used to define the thickness of a stroke in SVG?","options":"stroke-width\nborder-size\nline-width\nweight"},{"qText":"Which attribute defines the position of a rectangle’s top-left corner in SVG?","options":"x and y\nwidth and height\ntop and left\npos-x and pos-y"},{"qText":"Which attribute defines the radius of a circle in SVG?","options":"r\nradius\nrad\nsize"},{"qText":"Which SVG element allows drawing complex shapes using commands?","options":"<path>, <shape>, <draw>, <curve>"}]}]},{"id":"match","label":"Match the Following","type":"match","onlyBigScreen":true,"data":{"title":"Match the Following","fontSize":"1.5rem","canvasWidth":1200,"leftSideWidth":500,"allowFrac":false,"text":"Draws an oval shape | <ellipse cx=\"80\" cy=\"50\" rx=\"50\" ry=\"25\" />\nSets the outline color and thickness of a shape | stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"2\"\nDefines the SVG container where graphics are drawn | <svg> ... </svg>\nDraws a straight line between two points | <line x1=\"0\" y1=\"0\" x2=\"100\" y2=\"100\" />\nDraws a circle with center and radius | <circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"40\" />\nCreates a rectangle | <rect x=\"10\" y=\"10\" width=\"100\" height=\"50\" />\nFills the shape with color | fill=\"red\"\nDraws a closed shape by connecting multiple points (like a triangle) | <polygon points=\"30,10 50,60 10,60\" />"}},{"type":"classifySentence","label":"True or False","id":"true-false","data":{"title":"True or False","types":[{"name":"True","text":"SVG stands for Scalable Vector Graphics.\nSVG images can be scaled without losing quality.\nSVG is written in XML format.\nYou can style SVG elements using CSS.\nAn SVG file can contain shapes, paths, and text."},{"name":"False","text":"SVG is a raster image format like JPEG.\nSVG files cannot be animated.\nThe <circle> element is used to draw oval shapes.\nSVG cannot be embedded directly in HTML.\nSVG is not supported by modern web browsers."}]}},{"id":"fillup","label":"Fill in the blanks","type":"fillup","data":{"title":"Fill in the blanks","fontSize":"1.4rem","text":"SVG images are based on *xml (json, html)*.\nThe attribute used to set the color of an SVG shape is *fill (background, paint)*.\nThe <rect> element is used to draw a *rectangle (polygon, ellipse)*.\nThe attribute that controls the outline of an SVG shape is *stroke (border, outline)*.\nTo draw an oval in SVG, we use the *ellipse (polygon, path)* element.\nSVG images can be styled using *css (sql, php)*.\nSVG graphics are *resolution independent (pixel based, raster only)*.\nAn SVG element can be directly embedded inside *html (jpeg, pdf)*."}}]}